    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A gem or diamond cut style existing as early as the early fifteenth century. The natural octahedron was made flat on both the table and pavilion sides.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
